<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Attends Beijing New Year's Opera Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin and
other Party and state leaders Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing, and other
high-ranking officials watched the '97 New Year Beijing Opera
Evening Party, along with more than 1,000 people in the Chinese
capital this evening.
</P>
<P>
The Huairen Hall in Zhongnanhai, the site of the Party Central
Committee and the State Council, was blanketed by the first
snowfall this winter and echoed with the music of strings and
woodwinds, gongs and drums.
</P>
<P>
The new year's eve party was sponsored by the Ministry of
Culture and the Ministry of Broadcast, Film and Television.
</P>
<P>
Leading artists of different schools of Beijing opera, like
Shang Changrong, Geng Qichang, and Li Weikang entertained the
audience with the traditional artistic form.
</P>
<P>
Some young disciples of the opera also showed the vigor of
Beijing opera and drew several rounds of applauses for their
performing.
</P>
<P>
After the performances, Jiang Zemin and other Chinese officials
went onto the stage to congratulate the performers on their
success and to wish the audience a happy new year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
