<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Calls on HK People to Unite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief
Executive designate of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR), today called on the Hong Kong people to unite to create a
better Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In his new year message to Hong Kong people in a TVB's live
program, Tung said that the year of 1997 marks the beginning of a
new era for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that on July 1, 1997, when Hong Kong returns to her
motherland, the principles of "One Country, Two Systems", "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "high-degree autonomy" will
be implemented.
</P>
<P>
He said that after Hong Kong's handover, Hong Kong will have a
brighter future, adding that the pessimistic views on Hong Kong's
future has been bygones.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the future HKSAR government and the members of
the Provisional Legislative Council will make joint efforts to
serve the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
He assured the public that he and his HKSAR government will set
great store by the livelihood issue in the territory, while urging
the Hong Kong citizens to remember there are still some people who
are living in poverty.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Hong Kong people to have confidence in the
future HKSAR government and the PLC, claiming that they can
overcome all difficulties ahead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
