<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Stock market Ends With Key Industrial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's stockmarket, one of
Africa's largest stock markets, today ended the trading year
on a high note, with the key industrial index reaching an all-time
high of 8,786.26 points.
</P>
<P>
The index edged up another four points to draw the curtain on a
year that was characterised by a protracted bull-run caused by
increased foreign and institutional investor participantion, an
anticipated good agricultural season as well as falling interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
From just below 5,000 points at the end of last year, the index
has had a roller-coaster performance during the year to hover around
the 8,000-point mark during the greater part of the year.
</P>
<P>
Falling investment rates in the money market have discouraged most
investors, forcing them to turn to the stockmarket for better returns
on their investments.
</P>
<P>
In minings, trading continued quiet with coal producedr, Wankie,
edging up 40 cents to end the year at 600.
</P>
<P>
The mining index put on 18 points to close at 1,083.66 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
