<HEADLINE> Reviving Beef Industry Urged in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Cattle
Producers Association of Zimbabwe Les Mallet today called for
investment and funding to revive the country's beef industry.
</P>
<P>
Mallet appealed to the Agricultural Finance Corporation and
the Cold Storage Company to support the initiative and consider
operating medium-term cattle finance.
</P>
<P>
He also welcomed the easing of interest rates, saying if the
trend continued, it would become easier for the beef industry,
currently facing viability problems, to raise funds on the local
money market for on-lending.
</P>
<P>
Interest rates this year fell from above 30 percent by three
percentage points due to the fall in the reserve bank rediscount
rate, Mallet said, adding that it is the association's wish that the
year be as good as 1996.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the drought period of the 1991/92 season, the
national herd stood at approximately seven million and after the
drought, the number was reduced to less than four million.
</P>
</TEXT>
