<HEADLINE> Angola, France Sign Humanitarian Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Angola and France today signed
an agreement on humanitarian assistance under which France will
provide to Angola nine million Francs in aid.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the agreement, the money will be used to
finance the resettlement of Angolans who have become refugees
during the prolonged civil war as well as carders' training.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister for Social Assistance and Resettlement Albino
Malungo and Head of the French cooperation and cultural action
delegation,Jean Louis Riddell signed the agreement on behalf
their respective government. 
</P>
