the Serbian assembly after election results were reinstated,.
</P>
<P>
The opposition coalition Zajedno (Together), formed by the SPO
with the Democratic Party and the Serbian Civil Alliance, has been
organizing demonstrations and rallies to protest against the
annulment of the local election results. The political
confrontation between the opposition and the Serbian government
has caused a crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Kovacevic told a press conference in Belgrade that dialogue
between the authorities and opposition on media, election
conditions and overall transformation of society was necessary.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, this dialogue could take place only after
"local election results are recognized."
</P>
<P>
"We are for dialogue, because Serbia cannot become an equal
partner of the international community, as it deserves, without
it," Kovacevic said.
</P>
<P>
The recognition of the annulled local election results was one
of the key demands of the opposition to cease massive
demonstrations and hold dialogue with the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian parliament speaker proposed a panel debate last
week among the assembly deputies on the settlement of the
political crisis in Serbia, but the opposition, which has
boycotted most of the parliament sessions, has refused to take
part in the panel. 
</P>
