<HEADLINE> Stoneware and Animal Fossils Unearthed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Stoneware and fragments of
animal fossils from the early Stone Age have been unearthed at the
construction site of the largest commercial center in downtown
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The relics, the oldest ever found in Beijing's downtown core
area, were discovered some 12 m underground in the construction
zone of Oriental Square in Wangfujing, a well-known commercial
street in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Chinese paleontologists say that the site was a lake in the
late period of the early Stone Age.
</P>
<P>
The find sheds light on the study of the city's ancient
environment, the experts say. 
</P>
