<HEADLINE> China's Demand for Integrated Circuits in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China's demand for integrated
circuit blocks for program-controlled switchboards is estimated at
more than 84 million this year, according to "People's Post and
Telecommunications News", and blocks for mobile phones and pagers
at 20 million.
</P>
<P>
The country's demand for program-controlled switchboards in
1997 is estimated at 18 million lines, a little higher than the
country's production of 14 million lines.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to produce more than 85 million telephones,
80 percent of which will be for export. Most of the telephones
will be produced in Shanghai, and in Fujian and Guangdong
provinces, with the annual output in Guangdong's Huizhou city
expected to hit 30 million.
</P>
<P>
The country also plans to produce 1.5 million mobile phones and
over four million pagers, with most of the mobile phones produced
by Dongfang Telecommunications Co. Ltd., and Sino-foreign joint
ventures funded by NEC, Ericsson, and Nokia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
