<HEADLINE> Minor Earthquake Jolts Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 31 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring
5.9 on the Richter scale shook the Pacific coast of Chiapas State
in Mexico this morning.
</P>
<P>
So far, there have been no reports of casualties or property
damage.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's National Seismological Service (NSS) said the
epicenter was located at 15.67 degrees north latitude and 93.45
degrees west longitude.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, said the government agency, was felt in several
areas of the states of Tabasco and Chiapas about 1,000 kilometers
southeast to the country's capital of Mexico City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
