<HEADLINE> 1.5 Tons Of Marijuana Seized in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's Federal Judicial
Police have seized nearly 1.5 tons of marijuana and arrested one
person in a recent drug bust in the northern state of Tamaulipas.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Attorney-General's Office said today that the
seizure was made at a checkpoint of the Reynosa-Monterrey federal
highway when police stopped a truck for inspection.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver, a suspected drug trafficker, was immediately
taken into custody, according to a press bulletin released by the
office.
</P>
<P>
But the office did not say when the seizure was made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
