<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Attracts More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- One billion US dollars of
overseas investment flowed into south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region last year, 4.2 percent more than the 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
The total investment was the combination of 750 million US
dollars of direct investment and 250 million US dollars in loans,
a local trade official said here recently.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide, investment structure has become more rational, and
the focus of foreign investment has expanded from the previously
favored industries of processing, tourism and properties to
communication, energy and some pillar businesses.
</P>
<P>
The investment forms are diversified, including exclusive
foreign funds, joint ventures, cooperation, loans, bonds,
transfers of land use rights and the listing of shares on overseas
stock markets.
</P>
<P>
Major overseas-funded projects included an expressway that
links the region's capital city of Nanning with Beihai City and
the Fushi and Nanshan hydroelectric power stations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
