<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wasmosy Sacks Military Officers Loyal to Former General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Paraguayan President Juan
Carlos Wasmosy signed a decree today to retire the military
officers loyal to former disobedient commander of the army,
General Lino Cesar Oviedo, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The decree was the result of the indiscipline of officers who
backed General Oviedo last April when he refused to obey the
presidential order to go into retirement for an alleged coup
attempt.
</P>
<P>
On April 22, Oviedo took an army barrack with a group of
officers and sergeant majors loyal to him, in rebellion against
President Wasmosy's order to retire him as commander of the
country's army.
</P>
<P>
A spokesperson for the Paraguayan Presidency said that the
decree will become official Thursday during a ceremony marking the
promotions of high-ranking officers.
</P>
<P>
Several officers involved in the decree claimed that they will
resort to the court to fight the order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
