<HEADLINE> Suzhou Industrial Park in Shape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China will build 12 major
construction projects in Suzhou Industrial Park, the largest such
project between China and Singapore as the first phase development
is expected to complete this year.
</P>
<P>
As the first phase program, five out of eight square kilometers
of land development have already completed, along with 14
kilometers of highway, 19 bridges, a waterworks, a sewage
treatment plant, a gasworks and a substation and 70,000 square
meters of commercial and residential buildings.
</P>
<P>
According to Xie Jiabing, a spokesman for the park
administration committee, the industrial park has introduced 81
investment projects with 2.5 billion US dollars in foreign
investment, of which 540 million US dollars has already arrived
since the park started construction on May 12, 1994.
</P>
<P>
By now, 54 industrial projects have already located the
park. Most of these investment, he said, comes from multinationals
based in Europe, the United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea
and singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
