<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Calls for Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga today called for unity to build a peaceful and
developed nation.
</P>
<P>
In today's New Year message, the president said she earnestly
hoped that the new year will be a blessed one bringing peace,
prosperity and happiness to all Sri Lankans.
</P>
<P>
Since assuming office two years ago, she said, her government
has accomplished much which it could be proud of. However there is
much more to be done and further targets to be achieved.
</P>
<P>
"At this critical juncture when the country faces grave
challenges, the larger interests of the nation require that all
resolve to act unitedly, shedding differences, political or
otherwise," the president said.
</P>
<P>
"Today our foremost objective should be to achieve peace and
rebuild the nation," she added. "This calls for a deep sense of
responsibility and duty by our country so that we may serve this
and future generations well."  
</P>
</TEXT>
