<HEADLINE> Fire Guts 173 Kiosks in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A fire ravaged 173 makeshift
kiosks at the Pasar Baru market in Ujungpandang City of South
Sulawesi Province, Indonesia, at dawn on Tuesday, the Antara News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said more than 200 small-scale traders stayed in the
makeshift kiosks under a plan of local authorities to construct a
six-story market.
</P>
<P>
An official estimated the losses caused by the fire at between
70 million to 100 million rupiah (29,914 to 42,735 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Head of Ujungpandang Subdistrict H. Hamzah Hasan said the local
police were investigating the cause of the fire.  
</P>
