<HEADLINE> Meeting Scheduled to Fortify Panama's Political Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, December 31 (Xinhua) -- A conference on fortifying
political parties in Panama is scheduled for January 15-18, 1997,
sources with the country's electoral court said today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the leaders of Panama's 10 existing political
organizations and of eight others that are being formed will
attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A major objective of the gathering is to compile and evaluate
the experiences and lessons of political parties in other
countries in achieving internal efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed at the meeting include, among others,
the application of management concepts for fulfilling the missions
of political parties, and the strategic objectives of a political
party.
</P>
<P>
Financed by the European Union, international dignitaries, such
as Moemi Sanin of Colombia, Rolando Araya and Victor Hugo Alfar of
Costa Rica, and Juan Rial of Uruguay, will join the event.
</P>
<P>
Sanin, a former Colombian Foreign Minister, will speak at the
conference on "the abilities, skills, leadership styles and
management of a political party," the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
