<HEADLINE> One Dead, 29 Injured in U.S. Highway Pile-ups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 31 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and
29 others injured in a series of chain-reaction crashes on
Tuesday, which involved at least 70 vehicles in dense fog on an
interstate highway in New Orleans, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Visibility was about 15 meters on the bridge across Lake
Pontchartrain between New Orleans and Slidell when the accident
took place at 7:15 a.m. (1315 GMT), an Associated Press report
said.
</P>
<P>
A 34-year-old woman from New Orleans was killed and two people
were critically injured and at least 27 others went to hospitals
with minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
The highway was shut down for eight hours following the
pile-ups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
