<HEADLINE> South Africans Beat Switzerland Without Winning A Set </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- South Africa scored a 2-1
victory over Switzerland without winning a set in the Hopman Cup
mixed teams tennis championship in Perth on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Marc Rosset dominated the clash against Wayne Ferreira and led
6-0, 2-0 before he collided with a ball girl as he chased a ball
into the tramlines at the net.
</P>
<P>
He tumbled and landed heavily, immediately clutching at his
lower back.
</P>
<P>
Ferreira automatically won the singles 0-6, 1-2 on default and
the South African pair took the mixed doubles by forfeit after
Rosset's injury failed to respond to treatment.
</P>
<P>
Teen ace Martina Hingis had earlier given Switzerland a 1-0
lead with an 6-1, 6-2 win over Amanda Coetzer.
</P>
<P>
The victory lifted third-seeded South Africa's record in the
round-robin event to 2-0, while second-seeded Switzerland dipped
to 1-1.  
</P>
