<HEADLINE> Oriental Trounces Ducks in New Year's Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Oriental won its New
Year's game with a 91-72 victory over Beijing Ducks in its ninth
consecutive wins of the Chinese Basketball League this season.
</P>
<P>
The win kept Shanghai to share socond place with Liaoning
Hunters with a 9-2 record after 11-round competitions in the
12-team league, one win shy of the Army Rockets who lost to
Liaoning last week.
</P>
<P>
Lithunian Saulius Stombergas scored a game-high 31 points and
nine rebounds to lead The Oriental, which took a 49-43 halftime
lead.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's 18-6 run 9:30 minutes into the second half extended
the score to 67-49, also confirming its winning situation.
</P>
<P>
Bateer, 2.10-meter center, contributed 27 points and 14
rebounds for Beijing, held to only 29 points in the second half.
</P>
<P>
"This was one of the worst games we played this season," said
Yuan Chao, head coach of the Ducks, which were a 4-7 record. "We
were bad defensevily and offensevily, espcially in the second
half."
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, a new team this season with two Lithunians and four
non-Shanghai native players, just lost first two games this season
to Army Rockets and Guangdong Tigers apiece.
</P>
<P>
"We are happy for the results," Shanghai coach Li Qiuping
said. "Next step we will try to get a best place in the league."
</P>
<P>
The league will conclude in the end of March with 11-round
round-robin competitions and playoff games to play. 
</P>
