<DOCNO> XIE19970101.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President's New Year's Greetings (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today
hailed the achievements scored in China's reform, opening-up and
modernization drive, and extended greetings to non-Communist
parties, personages without any party affiliations, workers,
farmers, intellectuals and cadres, police officers and men, and
security officials, and to compatriots in Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao
and Chinese nationals from overseas.
</P>
<P>
At a new year's reception, Jiang, who is also general secretary
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, said that
China has made a good start in implementing the Ninth Five-Year
Plan (1996-2000) and Long-Range Objectives for the year 2010 for
national economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
China has maintained the momentum for rapid economic growth and
effectively curbed inflation, and further improved macro-economic
environment.
</P>
<P>
The country had good harvests despite natural calamities in
some of its areas, and reforms in its state-owned enterprises
accelerated, he said. Coastal areas have continued to excel and
the central and western parts of China have stepped up its pace
for growth. The country's hard currency reserves exceed the 100
billion US Dollar-mark.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, socialist democracy and development of
legality has progressed steadily, and still more prominence has
been given to the role of cultural and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that 1997 will be an extraordinary year in the
history of the development of the CPC and the Chinese nation, with
the convocation of the 15th National CPC Congress, which will map
out the strategic plan to further China's future reform,
development and stability, and with the Chinese government's
resumption of the exercise of its sovereignty over Hong Kong, an
important step toward the accomplishment of the motherland's
reunification.
</P>
<P>
Concerning economic development, Jiang said China will work
hard to advance two fundamental shifts, namely, shifting the
economy from the planned economy to the market one and shifting
the economic growth mode from being extensive to
intensive. Agriculture's role as the foundation will be
strengthened and reforms in the state-owned enterprises and their
pace for development will be further stepped up.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970101.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President's New Year Greeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China will also strive to accelerate readjusting the economic
structure, and keep improving macro-economic environment and
expanding foreign trade and raising the utilization ratio of
overseas investment, he said, adding that the people's material
and cultural life will further improve on the basis of economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, greater efforts will be made to promote cultural and
ethical progress in the new year in line with the decision adopted
by the Sixth Plenum of the 14 National CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong to the embrace of motherland is an
important event that will go down in history as splendid
achievements, and we will implement the policy of 'one country,
two systems' and exercise 'Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong'
with 'a high degree of autonomy'," he said.
</P>
<P>
With the backing of the central government and the Chinese
people, more than six million Hong Kong compatriots will certainly
make Hong Kong even more prosperous, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Taiwan, he explained, "We will also promote
contacts, exchanges, and cooperation across the Taiwan Straits in
line with the 'peaceful reunification' and 'one country, two
system' policies between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits."
</P>
<P>
"We welcome constructive views from different political parties
and groups and personalities from all walks of life in Taiwan on
relations across the Straits and on peaceful reunification. So we
hope that the Taiwan authorities, in keeping with principle of
righteousness of the Chinese nation, conform to the historical
trend of our times, cease all their activities that are aimed to
split the motherland and resort to actions practical in improving
cross-straits relations," he noted.
</P>
<P>
China's reforms, opening-up, and modernization drive require a
peaceful and stable international environment and the Chinese
government will strengthen friendly and cooperative relations with
neighboring countries and with all other countries around the
globe, based on the five principles of peaceful co-existence, he
noted, saying that "China will, as always, make further efforts to
establish a just, fair and reasonable international political and
economic order."
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, Jiang said he hopes that the people's political
consultative conference will strengthen political consultations
and democratic supervision, and go in for greater involvement in
political affairs in the new year, so as to contribute more to the
the country's economical development and all-round social
progress. 
</P>
