<HEADLINE> Party, State Leaders Attend CPPCC New Year's Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Communist Party and state
leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji,
Liu Huaqing, and Hu Jintao attended a new year's reception
held by the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
In addressing the reception, President Jiang Zemin hailed the
achievements of the country's reforms and opening-up and
modernization drive, and noted that China has made a good start in
its Ninth Five-Year Plan and Long-Range Objectives for the year
2010. China is prosperous and stable, and its people live in
harmony, he told those present.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and chairman of the Central Military Commission, called 1997
an extraordinary year in the history of the Party and the
country. He said that the Party will hold its 15th National
Congress which will further map out the strategic plan of future
reforms, development, and stability of the country and lead the
people throughout the country to advance the great cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics into the new
century.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, he said, China will also resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, something that represents an important
step towards the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
To be ready for danger in peacetime and to make a good
beginning to bring about a good finish are the extremely important
results of experiences gathered over a period of several thousand
years for running a country and exploring a cause, he said, adding
that, "we face heavy tasks in the reforms and construction, and
the times have high expectations for us."
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged the country's people to unite under the guidelines
of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and the party's basic line to achieve new victory in
socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and chairman of the CPPCC
National Committee, presided over the reception.
</P>
<P>
Among those present were also other high-ranking Party and
State leading officials, leaders of the CPPCC National Committee
and non-communist parties and All-China Federation of Industry
commerce, personages without party affiliations, and officials
from departments of the CPC Central Committee and the central
government, as well as representatives of all ethics from all
walks of life in Beijing.
</P>
</TEXT>
