<HEADLINE> London to Have "Bangla Town" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- London's Banglee-populated
Bricklane will soon be named "Bangla town," according to a press
report today.
</P>
<P>
The local government, the Tower Hamlet Council in London, has
agreed to name Bricklane "Bangla town" as a recognition to the
Bangladesh community in the UK and a working committee has been
formed for the purpose, committee chairman Mahmud A. Rauf was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshis now make up 65 percent of the population in
Bricklane while some 45,000 Bangladeshis live in the Tower Hamlet,
constituting 37 percent of total population of the council area.
Of the 50 councilors in the area, 14 are Bangladeshis.
</P>
<P>
A cultural center, a market of Bangladeshi goods and a model
Bangladeshi village will be set up in the future town representing
Bangladesh in Europe, Rauf explained, adding that two gates will
also be set up at both sides of the town while all the light posts
will be colored with Bangladesh's national flag colors -- red,
green and golden.
</P>
</TEXT>
