<HEADLINE> Rubin Shocks Majoli in Hopman Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- American Chanda Rubin ousted
Croatia's Iva Majoli in a women's singles clash at the Hopman Cup
tennis mixed teams tournament in Perth, Australia Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Rubin, 20, ranked 12th in the world, beat Majoli, 19, ranked
7th, in three sets, 6-3, 3-6, 7-6(7/3) over almost two hours.
</P>
<P>
Rubin's surprise success is a major upset to Croatia's hopes of
winning the tie and boosting their chances of reaching the final
of the contest they grabbed a year ago.
</P>
<P>
To win the tie, they will now be relying on world No four Goran
Ivanisevic to beat little known Justin Gimelstob in the men's
singles, and for Ivanisevic and Majoli to team up and overcome
the Americans in the mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, Majoli romped to a 4-0 lead in the
final set, but Rubin displayed marvellous grit in fighting back
to force a tie-breaker, which she won convincingly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
