<HEADLINE> Top Seed Advances at Gold Coast Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Brenda
Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands beat countrywoman Miriam
Oremans in a second-round match at the Gold Coast Classic tennis
tournament in Australia on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Oremans saved four set points in the first set tiebreaker
before losing. Schultz-McCarthy took only 22 minutes to wrap up
the second set and the match.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Russian Elena Likhovtseva also advanced to the third
round by defeating Romanian qualifier Catalina Cristea 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Sabine Appelmans of Belgium beat Sandrine Testud
of France 6-4, 6-4 and Ai Sugiyama of Japan, the sixth seed,
advanced with a 6-7 (5-7), 6-2, 6-3 win over Rita Grande of Italy.
</P>
<P>
Maria Louisa Serna of Spain upset fifth-seeded Ruxandra
Dragomir of Romania 6-4, 7-6 (7-1).
</P>
<P>
Rachel McQuillan of Australia, trying to break back into the
top 100, beat Germany's Barbara Rittner 7-5, 6-4 in blustery
conditions.
</P>
<P>
McQuillan was ranked as high as 28th in 1991, but injuries and
loss of form have seen her plummet to 186.
</P>
<P>
Her win over Rittner, ranked at 47, and her first-round
three-set victory over Taiwan's Shi-Ting Wang, also a top 40
player, should see McQuillan improve her ranking in this
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Katarina Studenikova of Slovakia was forced to
retire in her match with Anne Gaelle Sidot due to a shoulder
injury. Sidot led 6-4, 1-1 when Studenikova made the decision to
retire. 
</P>
