<HEADLINE> HK Chinese Chamber of Commerce Holds New Year Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese General Chamber of
Commerce of Hong Kong gave a reception here today to mark the year
of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Tsang Hin-chi, chairman of the chamber, said that it is
significant to mark the New Year's Day for it is half year from
Hong Kong's returning to her motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the Chief Executive and Provisional
Legislative Council being elected, the preparations for the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) is now under way.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong will enter a new era featuring "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong" under high-degree autonomy.
</P>
<P>
He said that in addition to its participation in the
preparations for various celebrations on Hong Kong's handover, his
chamber will go all out to support preparations for the
establishment of the HKSAR and the operation of the HKSAR
government.
</P>
<P>
The chamber will also play an active role in uniting all
sectors in business circle for building a better Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
