guide us to work together for the good of our country and look
forward to a better Sierra Leone in the years ahead.''
</P>
<P>
diplomatic sources said the message seeks to reassure both the
government and sierra Leoneans that the peace agreement signed
between president Kabbah and the ruf leader on December 1 holds
water.
</P>
<P>
''The RUF is firmly committed to the peace process and the
nearly six-year war is now virtually at an end,'' it said.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the government today ordered that all
military checkpoints should be dismantled except five major ones
leading to the north, east and south of the country.
</P>
<P>
The statement, broadcast on state radio, said it will be
illegal for security personnel manning checkpoints to demand
money or goods from commuters.
</P>
<P>
It also warned security personnel including civil defense
units not ''to board any public transport while carrying arms."
</P>
