<HEADLINE> Verdy Kawasaki Wins Japan's Emperor's Cup Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Verdy Kawasaki scored a 3-0
victory over professional Japan League rival Sanfrecce Hiroshima
in the championship game Wednesday of the Emperor's Cup.
</P>
<P>
It was Kawasaki's first Emperor's Cup since it joined Japan's
inaugural professional league in 1993. Its predecessor, Yomiuri
FC, won the title three times in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Hiroshima was runner-up for the second straight year in Japan's
annual tournament, which includes high school, college and company
teams in addition to all 16 professional clubs. In last year's
final, Hiroshima lost 3-0 to the Nagoya Grampus Eight, also of the
Japan League.
</P>
<P>
Kawasaki's victory marked the fourth straight year that a
professional team has won the Emperor's Cup. The Kawasaki was the
Japan League champion in 1993 and 1994 but only seventh in the
past season.
