<HEADLINE> Trade on Ugandan-Zairean Border Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 trucks carrying
coffee, gold and timber are seen crossing the border from Zaire
into Uganda every day recently, the "New Vision" paper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The traders, most of them Ugandan soldiers and Tutsi rebels
who have controlled eastern Zaire since late October, then return
to Zaire with food and money.
</P>
<P>
There is no border security on the Zairean side.
</P>
<P>
"We always have clandestine business with Zairean people. It
is a black market, but currently nobody seems to stop us," an
unidentified bussinessman was quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
