<HEADLINE> Malaysian Wins Tour of South China Sea Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian cyclist Muhamad Suhaimi
Keton won the gold cup this morning at the 5th and final leg of
the Tour of South China Sea Cycling Race, clocking 58:59 after
finishing 44 kilometers of circuit race.
</P>
<P>
His fellow cyclist Nor Effandy Rosli, who scored the second
place in the 4th leg of the race here on Tuesday, got another
second place today at 59:00. The third place was taken home by a
South Korea cyclist Chang Sheng Kaz, who also clocked at 59:00.
</P>
<P>
The trio took the lead at the 17th round of the 1.1 kilometers
long circuit, beating others by more than ten seconds.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the Malaysia team took home the group title, while
Wong Kam Po of Hong Kong won the best time award, and Rosli the
best score award.
</P>
<P>
The second Tour of South China Sea Cycling Race is expected to
be kicked off in January 1998, and some European teams will be
invited, said Cai Jiadong, chairman of the Chinese Cycling
Association, which co-sponsored the current race.
</P>
<P>
"We want to improve the level of the race, and renew the race
year by year," he told Xinhua. "We have had a very good start at
the current race."  
</P>
</TEXT>
