<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cherkasov Advances into Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, Australia (Xinhua) -- Wild card entry Andrei
Cherkasov of Russia advanced into the last eight of the 328,000
U.S. dollars Australian Hardcourt tennis championship in Adelaide
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cherkasov scored a surprise 6-2, 7-6 (15-13) win over
Australian Davis Cup squad member Patrick Rafter, who had a
three-month layoff with a number of niggling injuries.
</P>
<P>
The world 149th-ranked Cherkasov was given a wild card after
defending champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov asked tournament organizers
that his training partner be included in the draw.
</P>
<P>
Swede Mikael Tillstrom also entered the quarterfinals by being
awarded a walkover when Byron Black of Zimbabwe withdrew from
their second-round match citing viral flu.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Alex O'Brien of the United States progressed with
a 6-4, 3-6, 6-4 win over another Swede, Thomas Johannson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
