<HEADLINE> Visit China '97 Inaugurated on New Year's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Visit China '97, the event
highlighting China's tourism business for this year, was
inaugurated in Beijing's Capital International Airport today.
</P>
<P>
Heads of China's tourism and civil aviation authorities, and
the Beijing municipal government, came to meet the Air China's
CA932 flight from Frankfurt, which landed at the airport at 11:20
a.m. and carried the first overseas tourist group to visit China
this year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the inauguration ceremony, He Guangwei, director of
China National Tourism Administration (CNTA), said 16 new travel
routes and 48 tourism festivals have been specially designed for
those visiting China this year.
</P>
<P>
He added the travel industry will also launch another drive to
improve its service in more than 60 cities.
</P>
<P>
The CNTA estimates that more than 49 million overseas tourists
will visit China this year, creating about 11 billion US dollars
worth of revenues in foreign exchange. China's tourism revenues in
foreign exchange for the first time surpassed 10 billion US
dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
One of the sponsors of Visit China '97, the Civil Aviation
Administration of China will open 89 new air routes, including
nine international ones, and bigger discounts will be offered to
group travelers who take the flights of Chinese carriers to China.
</P>
<P>
Francesco Frangialli, secretary-general of the World Tourism
Organization, presented a congratulatory message to the event.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
