<HEADLINE> Mugabe Expresses Hope for Mid-East Solution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 1 (Xinhua) -- President Robert Mugabe has
expressed hope that Palestine and Israel would soon find a
peaceful solution to decades of conflict, now that the two sides
had agreed to meet and break the impasse.
</P>
<P>
''I also avail myself of the opportunity to observe
encouraging progress in the peace negotiations,'' Mugabe said in
his congratulatory message to Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on
his country's national day celebrations on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said, ''it is our hope that the new year will bring
renewed spirit to both sides, as they seek to consolidate the
gains already achieved over the protracted negotiations.''
</P>
<P>
Turning to bilateral relations between Zimbabwe and Palestine,
Mugabe said, ''i take this opportunity to reaffirm Zimbabwe's
firm commitment to furthering the strong ties between our two
peoples.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
