<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Athletics Chief Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Athletics Australia national
executive director Neil King resigned on Wednesday after seven
years in the job, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
King has come under great pressure with the Atlanta Olympic
doping controversy surrounding sprinter Dean Capobianco and
recently with his criticism of the funding cut to athletics by the
government-backed Australian Sports Commission.
</P>
<P>
But the governing body's newly-elected president Terry Dwyer
paid tribute to him in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He said King had overseen significant changes in the sport
including the establishment of the grand prix series and the
allocation of the International Amateur Athletics Federation
(IAAF) grand prix meeting to Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
